feederwatch %>% 
  group_by(latitude , longitude) %>% 
  summarise(how_many = sum(how_many)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(y=longitude , x=latitude)) +
  geom_point()

`summarise()` has grouped output by 'latitude'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

us_birds <- feederwatch %>% 
  mutate(country = substr(subnational1_code , 0,2) , 
         state = substr(subnational1_code , 4 , 5)) %>% 
  filter(country == 'US' , valid == 1)
us_birds %>% 
  group_by(species_code , state ) %>% 
  summarise(n = n() , sum = sum(how_many) , avg = sum/n ) %>% 
  arrange(desc(sum))

`summarise()` has grouped output by 'species_code'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
